headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 25 points, Lou Williams added 22 in his best game since returning to Atlanta and the surging Hawks pulled away in the final period for a 112-96 victory over the Orlando Magic on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 25, Williams 22, Hawks defeat Magic 112-96

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — RJ Barrett scored 18 of his 24 points in the third quarter and the New York Knicks beat the Charlotte Hornets 109-97 on Tuesday night for their seventh straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks beat Hornets 109-97, run winning streak to 7 games

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving capped a 32-point performance with a tough turnaround jumper, a driving layup through converging defenders and four free throws in the final minute, and the Brooklyn Nets held on for a 134-129 victory over the reeling New Orleans...
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving leads short-handed Nets past Pelicans, 134-129

events.name: LA Clippers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Paul George had 33 points, including two free throws with 4.8 seconds left that gave the Los Angeles Clippers a 113-112 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paul George has 33, Clippers down the Blazers 113-112

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 25 points and a season-high 18 rebounds, and the Minnesota Timberwolves pulled away over the final five minutes and thumped the Sacramento Kings 134-120 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves beat Kings for second time this season, 134-120
